{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Soak gelatine leaves in a bowl of cold water. Meanwhile, place raspberry purée, lemon juice and Kirsch in mixing bowl then heat <nobr>5 min\/90°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Squeeze out gelatine leaves, add to mixing bowl then mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Transfer to a large metal bowl then refrigerate. Clean mixing bowl.","Place a small bowl on mixing bowl lid then weigh in 100 g sugar. Remove bowl from lid."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place egg whites and salt in mixing bowl then, without measuring cup, whisk <nobr>9 min\/70°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. With 5 minutes remaining, slowly add reserved sugar. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Clean mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place cream in mixing bowl and whip <nobr>speed 3<\/nobr> until lightly whipped, watching carefully to avoid over-whipping.","Place chilled raspberry mixture over a bowl of ice until it starts to thicken (see tip). Fold through meringue and whipped cream. Pipe into glasses and refrigerate until ready to decorate and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 gelatine leaves","250 g raspberry purée","10 g lemon juice","10 g Kirsch or cherry brandy","100 g sugar","60 g egg whites, from medium eggs","1 pinch fine sea salt","250 g whipping cream"]}],"id":"r146792","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-KNcw0PRy1bA\/XZWfJC2Qy4I\/AAAAAAAAe_c\/_Z8O1uzQa0gmybRwLgBnEse-6oh2y-eNwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_p1Y5izJBPpDaqAJ8.png","title":"Piped Raspberry Mousse","publishedAt":"2017-08-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.5 g","fat":"25.3 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"30.3 g","calories":"1586 kJ \/ 381 kcal"},"usefulItems":"metal bowl, piping bag and plain nozzle, dessert glasses, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own raspberry purée, blend <nobr>350 g<\/nobr> fresh raspberries <nobr><strong>30 sec\/speed 9<\/strong><\/nobr>, then pass through a fine sieve to remove seeds.","Using a metal bowl allows you to chill the raspberry mixture faster.","A good sign of a mixture thickening is that it leaves a trail that holds it's shape momentarily when you drizzle it back into the bowl from a spoon."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h","4 portions"]}